Sentece: The systemic clearance of vincristine was 63% higher (925 +/- 61 versus 569 +/- 76 mL/min [mean +/- SEM]; P = .004), the elimination half-life was 35% shorter (12.7 +/- 0.6 versus 19.4 +/- 3.6 hours; P = .13), and the total area under the plasma concentration-time curve was 43% smaller (37.3 +/- 2.4 versus 65.1 +/- 10.1 ng x h/mL; P = .04) in patients who were receiving carbamazepine or phenytoin than in the control group.
Title: Cytochrome P450-inducing antiepileptics increase the clearance of vincristine in patients with brain tumors.
